spans.text: ( So long unclosed , they've watched thy doubtful Cure ) To his Hephaestion Alexander writes , To sooth thy Days
thy doubtful Cure ) To his Hephaestion Alexander writes
O ! that I could impart , As well my vital Spirits to thy Heart
well my vital Spirits to thy Heart
The Bird of Jove fans the supporting Air , Above my Plume does his broad Wings display
to the wavering Host the auspicious Sight
at once the Empire of the East
the Flood TO overmatch the Boilings of my youthful Blood
from thine to learn their Monarch's State
those Crowns , which at my Feet they lay , Forget the ambitious Subject of their Speed
those Crowns , which at my Feet they lay , Forget the ambitious Subject of their Speed
at first to gaze Upon the Charms of her unguarded Face
to gaze Upon the Charms of her unguarded Face
the Charms of her unguarded Face
Name alone she sighs , and moves
I for lost Clytus shed , And wept more Drops
how much that Passion must transcend
in the vanquished Earth , A Brother , not imposed upon my Birth , Too weak a Tie unequal Thoughts to bind
Too weak a Tie unequal Thoughts
thought only fit for Monarch over the rest
only fit for Monarch over the rest
